title: Barbecued Leg Of Lamb
summary: Need a gluten free and dairy free main course? Barbecued Leg Of Lamb could be a spectacular recipe to try. One serving contains 1376 calories, 99g of protein, and 61g of fat. For $10.09 per serving, this recipe covers 71% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe serves 4. 1 person has made this recipe and would make it again. A mixture of soy sauce, curry powder, vinaigrette to dress, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so delicious. To use up the ground cumin you could follow this main course with the Moroccan Chocolate Mousse as a dessert. It is brought to you by BBC Good Food. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes around 2 hours and 51 minutes. Overall, this recipe earns an outstanding spoonacular score of 85%. Similar recipes are Barbecued Leg of Lamb, Barbecued Lamb, and Barbecued Lamb Kabobs.
